  "text": "Previous research in internationalization has generally acknowledged the existence of different export channel strategies, varying on the basis of the degree of control exerted by the firms and the required resources [CITATION_1] . In particular, two main exporting strategies can be identified: direct exporting, where firms establish direct contact with overseas customers; and indirect exporting, where firms distribute their products in international markets through an intermediary [CITATION_2] .",
